    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors satisfy Gradation 1 by inspection and are appropriately scoped out of formal assessment per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The UQ campaign documented in VR-CPB-2026-01 appendix B demonstrates that geometric and boundary-condition uncertainties produce less than 4 % variation in the NIH QoI, supporting the conclusion that the CFD model is sufficiently credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met at all five operating points. The assessment team concludes that the model credibility is adequate for the stated COU at the Medium assurance level.",
